
= About the project =

== What are we working on? ==

First of~all, Luwrain is an~operating system with an attempt to~apply some new ideas  and any available  experience in~area of~OS design  for~needs of~blind persons.
Current time to do this work is very fortunate 
as Android, Tizen and FirefoxOS made it easy to~realize 
that Linux turned~out as~a~wonderful base for~popular devices and in~same time it~remains  publicly available for~using by~everybody.
Once you get proper understanding of~LInux world
you get a~clew what you should do if you'd like to~create cutting-edge technology.
We'd like to~treat that fact as~a~good chance for~solution of~rather  difficult problems in~area of~assistive technologies 
as we never had before.

Meantime one important thing should be clarified especially detailly.
a~lot of~usual gadgets based on popular mobile OS like Android or  something like that 
very often  eventually are~considered   by~their users  as~not~more valuable than some sort of~modern toys.
In case of assistive  technologies any doubts 
what exactly devices~are:   an~irreplaceable tool or an~item for~entertainment, are   completely improper.
They are always the~former because disabled persons are not~able to~do~without them.
Such helpful things are not able to become boring and users will not give~up them.

Finally, we guess we~are able to~describe the~project philosophy  precisely  
with the~following 10 brief statements:

# It is an OS completely designed for blind and visually impaired persons.
# It must be convenient, fast and clearly understandable.
# It~has~to support various languages and localizations.
# It aims to be~sutable for~desktop computers as~well~as for mobile work.
# It is~based on~the~Linux kernel and other FOSS software.
# No any bias towards any particular  hardware type.
# It~is non-profitable project.
# Its auditory is all users who need it.
No~matter what experience  they got, 
what country are they from,
what profession are they occupied~in and so~on.
# Everybody is~able to~participate in~its development.
but authors want to~keep high quality and urge everybody to~respect accepted quality requirements for~all incoming patches.
# We believe available experience in~GNU/Linux world is~enough at~least to~start this work and gives good base for~success.

